{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Mirror"], "type": "title", "extent": [33, 44], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [44, 118], "text": ["Duplicates and mirrors objects or geometry across a mirror plane."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [133, 205], "text": ["Mirror works at both the ", {"text": ["Scene and Geometry levels"], "fullpath": "/basics/objects", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/basics/objects"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [529, 684], "text": ["This is useful for rigging one side of a ", {"text": ["character"], "fullpath": "/character/index", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/character/"}, " and then duplicating the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/OBJ/bone", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "OBJ/bone"}, {"text": ["Bones"], "fullpath": "/nodes/obj/bone", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/obj/bone"}, " to the other side."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["At the Scene level, the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/mirror", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/mirror"}, {"text": ["Mirror"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/mirror", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/mirror"}, " tool creates new mirror duplicates of the selected objects. You can use the controls in the operation controls toolbar (across the top of the viewer) to automatically rename the objects as you duplicate them, for example ", {"text": ["r_arm"], "type": "code"}, " is mirrored as ", {"text": ["l_arm"], "type": "code"}, "."], "extent": [205, 529], "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet"}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [684, 804], "text": ["At the Geometry level, the tool creates a ", {"text": ["Mirror surface node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/mirror", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/mirror"}, " which mirrors the selected geometry."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text